      "type": "text",
      "text": "1. While we ate all kinds of sushi, I loved this one place that gave us miniature versions of the menu (completely edible)\n2. Convenience store eats are worth the hype\n3. Maid cafe curry (mostly for cuteness, not the taste)\n4. Soba :D\n5. Kaiseki at the ryokan - an interesting experience that I don’t want to revisit! I spoke with a few locals who also said they weren’t a fan of traditional Japanese foods.",
